value.text: radiating pain to the left arm

data.text: A 52-year-old male presented with chest tightness, breathlessness on exertion, and radiating pain to the left arm for the past 3 days. He has a history of hypertension and hyperlipidemia. A 29-year-old female complained of burning micturition, increased urinary frequency, and suprapubic discomfort. Urine dipstick was positive for nitrites and leukocytes. Diagnosed with urinary tract infection. Treated with nitrofurantoinfor 5 days.

A 34-year-old male reported a high-grade fever with chills, severe headache, myalgia, and retro-orbital pain. CBC revealed thrombocytopenia. NS1 antigen test returned positive. He was diagnosed with dengue fever. Managed with paracetamol and fluid resuscitation.

A 45-year-old female reported excessive thirst, frequent urination, and unintended weight loss. Fasting blood glucose was 215 mg/dL. Diagnosed with type 2 diabetes mellitus and started on metformin.

A 16-year-old boy presented with itchy eyes, sneezing, and nasal congestion for the past month, especially in the morning. Skin prick test was positive for pollen. Diagnosed with allergic rhinitis. Started on loratadine.

A 44-year-old female with neck swelling, heat intolerance, and palpitations. TSH levels were suppressed and T3/T4 elevated. Diagnosed with Graves’ disease. Treated with methimazole and propranolol.
